<dl id="n53050c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53050c">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53050c"> 50(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> gute sch&ouml;ne hand</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">[In the Middle Ages there was a German word for &lsquo;right&rsquo; (<i>zese</i>) that was replaced only later on by the metaphorical meaning of the good, the right hand (even today, people still say to children &mdash; Show your good nice hand (&lsquo;Gib <mark>das gute, das sch&ouml;ne H&auml;ndchen</mark>&rsquo;) <small> Fritz Mauthner, <a name="FMBK1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FMBK1"><cite title="source">Beitr&auml;ge zu einer Kritik der Sprache.</cite></a> 3 vols (1901-2) III 110</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
